Victoria Wasteney was suspended from her job after colleague Enya Nawaz accused her of trying to convert her to Christianity . 
  The senior occupational therapist prayed for her and invited her to church events . 
  She was given a written warning for misconduct and suspended for nine months . 
  She says she was branded a ‘religious nutcase’ and has launched an appeal against the East London NHS Trust . 
  She claims they discriminated against her freedom of conscience and religion . 
 